5770
Cairn scavengers are systematically stripping Measure's Rest of survey tablets and historical records that have no replacement value. The scavenger clan has grown large enough to hold the library complex against individual Warden patrols, and continued losses will render the Reach cartographic archive permanently incomplete. The Warden Commander requires a significant kill count before committing a full expulsion detail.
The cairn scavenger presence at Measure's Rest has been reduced below operational density. The Warden Commander has dispatched a lockdown team to secure the remaining survey tablet collection, and a provisional inventory is underway to assess what records were lost. The expulsion operation has been logged as a standing precedent for future archive defense protocols.

